If you've never used one of
these ice cream machines before,

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:57.180
they're pretty simple.

00:04:57.180 --> 00:04:59.120
This container goes in
the freezer for several hours

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:01.060
to lower the temperature quite a bit,

00:05:01.060 --> 00:05:04.620
and then it just holds your liquid
while it spins in this machine.

00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:07.140
Let's turn this on,
and pour in our mix.

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:14.300
[Music]

00:05:14.300 --> 00:05:16.120
The ice cream machine
method is very simple,

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:17.120
but it does take some time,

00:05:17.120 --> 00:05:18.300
and while that's running,

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:19.640
let's get our next batch started.

00:05:19.640 --> 00:05:23.090
[Music]

00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:25.140
This time, we're using the blender recipe,

00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:26.720
and with the blender recipe,

00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:30.460
we now need to add three
cups of ice into our blender,

00:05:30.460 --> 00:05:32.280
and then pour our mixture over that.

00:05:32.280 --> 00:05:36.400
We don't add any water because
the melting ice will dilute it enough.

00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:43.300
[Music]

00:05:43.300 --> 00:05:45.160
Once we blend up the ice,

00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:47.880
this version of the frozen
hot chocolate is complete.

00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:49.140
Cheers.

00:05:49.140 --> 00:05:52.140
[Music]

00:05:52.140 --> 00:05:55.400
The blender version gives
a much thinner consistency

00:05:55.410 --> 00:05:57.090
than the other three methods.

00:05:57.090 --> 00:05:58.490
So if you want a
version that you drink,

00:05:58.490 --> 00:06:00.040
rather than eat with a spoon,

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:01.260
this is the way to go.

00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:05.360
Oh it's so good.

00:06:05.840 --> 00:06:06.539
There we go.

