It has taken maybe 15-ish minutes,

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:10.780
and at this point,

00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:14.889
our ice cream machine's
frozen hot chocolate

00:06:14.889 --> 00:06:17.380
is just the right consistency.

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:25.700
[Music]

00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:26.700
That's so good.

00:06:37.780 --> 00:06:39.120
I can do this all day.

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:43.900
As you can see, the ice cream maker
does give us a little bit thicker

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:46.440
of a consistency than when
we make it in the blender.

00:06:46.440 --> 00:06:49.180
For our next method, we're going
to be using something you may have done

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:51.120
if you've ever made ice cream at home.

00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:53.919
That involves putting what
we're going to freeze in a Ziploc bag,

00:06:53.919 --> 00:06:56.020
and putting that bag
inside of a bigger bag,

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:58.680
and filling the bigger
bag full of ice and salt.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:03.960
I have here a 1 gallon freezer bag,
and a 2 gallon freezer bag.

00:07:03.960 --> 00:07:06.620
So we've got our smaller one gallon bag.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:08.259
We're going to pour
our mix into there

00:07:08.259 --> 00:07:10.949
after adding the cream,
the milk, and the water.

00:07:10.949 --> 00:07:12.789
That's about 3 cups of cool liquid.

00:07:12.789 --> 00:07:14.540
So this is just room temperature.

00:07:14.540 --> 00:07:16.980
We don't have to worry
about it melting the bag, or anything.

00:07:16.980 --> 00:07:20.710
[Music]

00:07:20.710 --> 00:07:23.020
Squeeze out as much of the air as we can.

00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:26.780
Now, we just have a
bag full of liquid chocolate.

00:07:27.060 --> 00:07:29.500
Now, we have our bag
of ice and a bunch of salt,

00:07:29.509 --> 00:07:30.920
I'm using ice cream salt,

00:07:30.930 --> 00:07:32.779
you can use other salt if you like.

00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:34.400
It should all work just as well.

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:41.560
[Music]

00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:43.819
Using about 8 cups of ice,

00:07:43.819 --> 00:07:46.580
and now, we'll add about
one cup of our salt.

00:07:46.580 --> 00:07:50.080
[Music]

00:07:50.080 --> 00:07:52.500
Get the salt and ice nice
and mixed up together,

00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:54.560
and now we take our smaller bag,

00:07:56.420 --> 00:07:59.060
put it inside our larger bag.

00:07:59.680 --> 00:08:02.540
Let's just make sure it's
nice and covered with our ice.

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:05.860
[Music]

00:08:05.860 --> 00:08:10.440
I'm going to try and suck some
of the extra air out of this bag as well.

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:16.720
[Music]

00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:19.000
That way all the ice should
pretty well stay in contact

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:20.000
with the bag inside.

00:08:20.660 --> 00:08:23.480
And at this point, we just
need to start mixing it up.

00:08:23.740 --> 00:08:26.760
We shake it,
and we squish it,

00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:27.960
and scrunch it.

00:08:27.960 --> 00:08:31.080
and just move it around
because we want all that salty ice

00:08:31.080 --> 00:08:32.649
to be cooling down the mixture,

00:08:32.649 --> 00:08:34.579
and we don't want it
to present to a solid piece.

00:08:34.580 --> 00:08:37.080
We want it to freeze into a nice slush.

00:08:37.080 --> 00:08:40.440
With this method, you can kind of
choose the consistency that you want.

00:08:40.800 --> 00:08:41.919
If you want it to be thicker,

00:08:41.920 --> 00:08:44.620
just keep it moving around in your
ice and salt for a little bit longer.

00:08:44.800 --> 00:08:46.820
A little bit more of
a drinkable consistency,

00:08:46.820 --> 00:08:47.840
just take it out sooner.

00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:49.900
[Music]

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:52.960
After about 10 minutes of mixing
our hot chocolate around

00:08:52.960 --> 00:08:54.840
inside that salty ice,

00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:59.380
we have what is most definitely
not that same liquid consistency.

00:08:59.380 --> 00:09:01.680
Now, let's rinse this off
so we don't accidentally end up

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:03.010
getting salt in our hot chocolate,

00:09:03.940 --> 00:09:05.500
and scoop it out,
and see what it looks like.

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.200
Of course I do want 
to rinse it very quickly

00:09:08.200 --> 00:09:09.780
so I don't warm it back up.

00:09:09.780 --> 00:09:21.060
[Music]

00:09:22.660 --> 00:09:23.660
We have one more method to try,

00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:25.360
and that is using liquid nitrogen.

00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:26.600
Let's whip up one more batch,

00:09:26.600 --> 00:09:30.400
and see how quickly we can make
frozen hot chocolate using that.

00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:40.840
[Music]

00:09:40.850 --> 00:09:41.850
There's our chocolatey base.

00:09:41.850 --> 00:09:43.621
Now, let's add some
liquid nitrogen to it,

00:09:43.621 --> 00:09:46.140
and see if we can
flash freeze this sucker.

00:09:46.140 --> 00:10:01.580
[Music]

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:04.060
All of the liquid nitrogen
down inside our mixture

00:10:04.060 --> 00:10:06.490
bubbling up is giving
it a really interesting

00:10:06.490 --> 00:10:08.160
frothy texture on top.

00:10:08.160 --> 00:10:19.200
[Music]

00:10:19.200 --> 00:10:22.080
As you can see, all four
of these methods work great.

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.860
Some people are going
to have an ice cream maker,

00:10:23.860 --> 00:10:24.620
some people won't.

00:10:24.620 --> 00:10:26.040
I think most people
will have a blender,

00:10:26.040 --> 00:10:29.520
but if not, Ziploc bags are
really easy to get your hands on,

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:31.180
and that method works just as well.

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:33.240
Of course, if you want
to get really fancy with it,

00:10:33.240 --> 00:10:36.400
you can start adding things
